name: hydroxylamine reductase
classes: Acting on other nitrogenous compounds as donors;
reaction: NH3 + H2O + acceptor = hydroxylamine + reduced acceptor [RN:R00284]
comment: A flavoprotein. Reduced pyocyanine, methylene blue and flavins act as donors for the reduction of hydroxylamine. May be identical to EC 1.7.2.1, nitrite reductase (NO-forming).

references.title: Ann. Acad. Sci. Fenn. Ser. A II 60 (1955) 200.
Cytochrome cd1, reductive activation and kinetic analysis of a multifunctional respiratory enzyme.
